# CVE-2026-43969 — cowlib: Cookie request-header injection via unvalidated
# encoder in cow_cookie:cookie/1 (severity: LOW).
#
# Suppressed because:
#   * No fixed release exists. Every published cowlib (2.9.0–2.16.1) is affected;
#     the only fix is an unreleased upstream commit, so there is no version to
#     bump to. cowlib here is a transitive dep of cowboy.
#   * Not reachable. cow_cookie:cookie/1 builds a *client-side* Cookie request
#     header (gun-style HTTP clients). This app has no gun dependency, uses
#     cowboy only as a server, and never calls cow_cookie; outbound HTTP uses
#     httpoison/hackney.
#
# REMOVE this entry once a patched cowlib is released on Hex and we bump to it.
CVE-2026-43969
